org.jorlib.frameworks.columnGeneration.colgenMain

Class AbstractColumn<T,V extends AbstractPricingProblem<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jorlib.frameworks.columnGeneration.colgenMain.AbstractColumn<T,V>

  • public abstract class AbstractColumn<T,V extends AbstractPricingProblem<T>>
extends Object
    Abstract Class modeling a column in the column generation procedure. Note that the fields in a column (except the value assigned to it by the master problem) are all final: a column should NOT be tempered with.
    Version:
    13-4-2015
    Author:
    Joris Kinable

      boolean isArtificialColumn
      Indicates whether this is a real column generated by a pricing problem, or whether it has been generated to obtain an initial feasible solution.
      double value
      The value of the column assigned to it by the last master problem solved which contained this node

    • Field Detail

      • value

        public double value
        The value of the column assigned to it by the last master problem solved which contained this node

      • isArtificialColumn

        public final boolean isArtificialColumn
        Indicates whether this is a real column generated by a pricing problem, or whether it has been generated to obtain an initial feasible solution. Optimal solutions may NOT contain artificial columns unless the problem is infeasible

      • creator

        public final String creator
        Textual description of the method which created this column, e.g a pricing problem, initial solution, artificial, etc. Used for debugging purposes only to determine where a column is coming from
